<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The struct embeds a string-with-length type that (in the provided codebase) exposes a non-const pointer to characters and that pointer is used only for reading. Specifically, if struct _MHD_str_w_len has a member declared as 'char *str;' then MHD_RqDAuthParam.value.str points to mutable characters even though functions (e.g. get_unquoted_param_copy) treat it as read-only (the param argument is 'const struct MHD_RqDAuthParam *'). This allows modification of the pointed-to characters through that pointer and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. Fix: change the inner pointer to point to a const-qualified type (e.g. 'const char *str;').
</scenario>
